Kiss (Keep It Simple Stupid). 
-------------------------------

About:
-------------------------------
A very lightweight mvc framework that uses propel (http://propelorm.org/)
as the Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) and bramus as the base router. 

Requres:
-------------------------------
 - PHP: 5.4
 - phpunit: 3.7+
 - mod_rewrite
 - Composer

Set up:
-------------------------------
$ clone https://github.com/scottyadean/kiss-cm.git kiss-app
$ cd kiss-app
$ cd app/library/
$ php composer.phar


Create a new Vhost:
-------------------------------
<VirtualHost *:80>
   DocumentRoot "/home/[your_path_here]/kiss/public"
   ServerName kiss.local
   
   # This should be omitted in the production environment
   SetEnv APPLICATION_ENV development

   <Directory "/home/[your_path_here]/kiss/public">
       Options Indexes MultiViews FollowSymLinks
       AllowOverride All
       Order allow,deny
       Allow from all
   </Directory>
   
</VirtualHost>


Create a host entry:
-------------------------------
127.0.0.1   kiss.local


Kiss your new app:
-------------------------------
http://kiss.local


Add new mvc:
-------------------------------
 ROUTE:
 - Edit the file:  app/libray/kiss/Router.php
 - In side the preexisting index route add a new action "hello"
 - $this->add("index", "/", array('index', 'about-us', 'hello'));
 
 ACTION:
 - Edit the file: app/controllers/Index.php
 - Add a new action method to the Index controller called helloAction,
 - public function helloAction() { }

 VIEW:
 - Create a new view in /app/kiss/views/index/hello.phtml
 - Inside your new hello.phtml file add <h1>Hello World</h1>

 TEST:
 http://kiss.local/index/hello

